  - 636
By: Li Jih-hua
---
The old painters worked in the same way as did the Buddha in explaining the
law. He spoke by natural inspiration, without any effort, about past kalpas,
their causes and effects, which manifest and dissolve in a mysterious fashion
beyond human comprehension, though never contrary to truth and reason.
